## ğŸš€ How to Use

### 1. Copy Files to Your Project

```bash
# Copy to your Flutter project's lib/core directory
cp core_constants_*.dart your_project/lib/core/constants/
cp core_theme_*.dart your_project/lib/core/theme/
cp core_utils_*.dart your_project/lib/core/utils/
cp core_errors_*.dart your_project/lib/core/errors/
cp core_network_*.dart your_project/lib/core/network/
```

### 2. Import in Your Code

```dart
// Constants
import 'package:catering_app/core/constants/app_constants.dart';
import 'package:catering_app/core/constants/firebase_constants.dart';
import 'package:catering_app/core/constants/route_constants.dart';

// Theme
import 'package:catering_app/core/theme/colors.dart';
import 'package:catering_app/core/theme/text_styles.dart';
import 'package:catering_app/core/theme/app_theme.dart';

// Utils
import 'package:catering_app/core/utils/validators.dart';
import 'package:catering_app/core/utils/formatters.dart';
import 'package:catering_app/core/utils/date_utils.dart';
import 'package:catering_app/core/utils/currency_utils.dart';

// Errors
import 'package:catering_app/core/errors/exceptions.dart';
import 'package:catering_app/core/errors/failures.dart';

// Network
import 'package:catering_app/core/network/network_info.dart';
import 'package:catering_app/core/network/api_response.dart';
```

### 3. Example Usage

```dart
// Using constants
final minOrder = AppConstants.minimumOrderValue;
final orderStatus = AppConstants.orderStatusPending;

// Using theme
MaterialApp(
  theme: AppTheme.lightTheme,
  darkTheme: AppTheme.darkTheme,
);

// Using validators
final emailError = Validators.validateEmail('test@example.com');
final passwordError = Validators.validateStrongPassword('MyPass123!');

// Using formatters
final formattedPrice = CurrencyUtils.formatWithSeparator(1234.56);
final formattedDate = AppDateUtils.formatDate(DateTime.now());

// Using error handling
try {
  // Some operation
} on AuthException catch (e) {
  // Handle auth error
  print(e.message);
} catch (e) {
  // Handle unknown error
  throw UnknownException(details: e);
}

// Using API response
final response = ApiResponse<User>.success(
  data: user,
  message: 'User fetched successfully',
);
```

